e\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#SeparableClosure\"><span class=\"name\">SeparableClosure</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"The absolute separable closure is defined to be the relative separable closure inside the\nalgebraic closure. It is indeed a separable closure (`IsSepClosure`) by\n`separableClosure.isSepClosure`, and it is Galois (`IsGalois`) by `separableClosure.isGalois`\nor `IsSepClosure.isGalois`, and every separable extension embeds into it (`IsSepClosed.lift`). ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#SeparableClosure","kind":"def","line":210,"name":"SeparableClosure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L210-L214"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure.isSepClosure\"><span class=\"name\">separableClosure</span>.<span class=\"name\">isSepClosure</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsSepClosed.html#IsSepClosed\">IsSepClosed</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsSepClosed.html#IsSepClosure\">IsSepClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">↥<span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\">separableClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span>)</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `E` is separably closed, then the separable closure of `F` in `E` is an absolute\nseparable closure of `F`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure.isSepClosure","kind":"instance","line":204,"name":"separableClosure.isSepClosure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L204-L208"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#IsSepClosed.separableClosure_eq_bot_iff\"><span class=\"name\">IsSepClosed</span>.<span class=\"name\">separableClosure_eq_bot_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsSepClosed.html#IsSepClosed\">IsSepClosed</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\">separableClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Bot.bot\">⊥</a> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsSepClosed.html#IsSepClosed\">IsSepClosed</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `E / F` is a field extension and `E` is separably closed, then the separable closure\nof `F` in `E` is equal to `F` if and only if `F` is separably closed. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#IsSepClosed.separableClosure_eq_bot_iff","kind":"theorem","line":193,"name":"IsSepClosed.