</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `i` is an `F`-algebra homomorphism from `E` to `K`, then the preimage of\n`separableClosure F K` under the map `i` is equal to `separableClosure F E`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure.comap_eq_of_algHom","kind":"theorem","line":102,"name":"separableClosure.comap_eq_of_algHom","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L102-L107"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#map_mem_separableClosure_iff\"><span class=\"name\">map_mem_separableClosure_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Hom.html#AlgHom\">→ₐ[</a><span class=\"fn\">F</span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Hom.html#AlgHom\">]</a> <span class=\"fn\">K</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">i</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\">separableClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">K</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\">separableClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"If `i` is an `F`-algebra homomorphism from `E` to `K`, then `i x` is contained in\n`separableClosure F K` if and only if `x` is contained in `separableClosure F E`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#map_mem_separableClosure_iff","kind":"theorem","line":96,"name":"map_mem_separableClosure_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L96-L100"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#mem_separableClosure_iff\"><span class=\"name\">mem_separableClosure_iff</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <span class=\"fn\">E</span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Membership.mem\">∈</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\">separableClosure</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Iff\">↔</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/Separable.html#IsSeparable\">IsSeparable</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"An element is contained in the separable closure of `F` in `E` if and only if\nit is a separable element. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#mem_separableClosure_iff","kind":"theorem","line":91,"name":"mem_separableClosure_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L91-L94"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure\"><span class=\"name\">separableClosure</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/IntermediateField/Basic.html#IntermediateField\">IntermediateField</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The (relative) separable closure of `F` in `E`, or called maximal separable subextension\nof `E / F`, is defined to be the intermediate field of `E / F` consisting of all separable\nelements. The previous results prove that these elements are closed under field operations. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.html#separableClosure","kind":"def","line":78,"name":"separableClosure","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableClosure.lean#L78-L87"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.FieldTheory.SeparableDegree","Mathlib.FieldTheory.IsSepClosed","Mathlib.RingTheory.AlgebraicIndependent.AlgebraicClosure"],"instances":[{"className":"Algebra.IsAlgebraic","name":"separableClosure.isAlgebraic","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"Algebra.IsSeparable","name":"separableClosure.isSeparable","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"IsGalois","name":"separableClosure.isGalois","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"IsSepClosure","name":"separableClosure.isSepClosure","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"IsSepClosed","name":"SeparableClosure.isSepClosed","typeNames":["SeparableClosure"]},{"className":"Algebra.IsSeparable","name":"IntermediateField.isSeparable_sup","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"Algebra.IsSeparable","name":"IntermediateField.isSeparable_iSup","typeNames":["Subtype"]},{"className":"NeZero","name":"Field.instNeZeroSepDegree","typeNames":["Field.sepDegree"]},{"className":"NeZero","name":"Field.instNeZeroInsepDegree","typeNames":["Field.insepDegree"]},{"className":"NeZero","name":"Field.instNeZeroFinInsepDegree","typeNames":["Field.finInsepDegree"]}],"name":"Mathlib.FieldTheory.SeparableClosure"}